This paper proposes a novel discriminative regression method for classification, which involves learning a more flexible and discriminative projection that preserves the intrinsic structure of data, possesses feature selection and interpretability properties, and avoids overfitting. These characteristics suggest that the paper could be relevant to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Sound (cs.SD).
